"Future University in Egypt - FUE\nThis institution has verified its data\nKhaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt: We have achieved success in interactive education\nhttps://www.dotmsr.com/News/196/1368767/\u062e\u0627\u0644\u062f-\u0639\u0632\u0627\u0632\u0649-\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633-\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633-\u0623\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0621-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062d\u0642\u0642\u0646\u0627-\u0646\u062c\u0627\u062d\u0627-\u0643\u0628\u064a\u0631\u0627\nWe are ready to take the first semester exams in light of the precautionary measures and the safety of students and faculty is our top priority We are committed to social responsibility and the university's activities have increased in light of the Corona crisis Future University in Egypt (FUE) is a pioneer in launching humanitarian initiatives and organizing medical convoys Investing in \"distance education\" is a win-win situation for all... and cooperation programs with international universities qualify students for the international labor market\nRead More\nA cooperation agreement between \u201cFuture University in Egypt\u201d and \u201cSchlumberger Egypt\u201d for training in \u201cPetroleum Engineering\u201d\nhttps://www.alnahar.news/21083\nIn continuation of the scientific approach that the Future University in Egypt (FUE) is taking under the auspices of Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees, which aims to create a new generation of graduates qualified to scientifically enter the labor market, a joint cooperation agreement was signed between the Future University and Schlumberger Egypt, in order to provide a training program aimed primarily Qualifying and training the students of the Petroleum Engineering Department at the College of Engineering and Technology by employing the various experiences and capabilities that the company enjoys in this field.\nRead More\nIn the presence of Hisham Arafat.. Tuesday.. The Faculty of Economics of the Future University in Egypt is holding a new episode of the \u201cFuture Policy Forum\u201d via \u201czoom\u201d technology\nhttps://www.elbyan.com/\u0628\u062d\u0636\u0648\u0631-\u0647\u0634\u0627\u0645-\u0639\u0631\u0641\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u062b\u0644\u0627\u062b\u0627\u0621-\u0643\u0644\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0642\u062a\u0635\u0627/\nThe Faculty of Economics and Political Science at Future University in Egypt (FUE)\u00a0will hold, the day after tomorrow, Tuesday, at noon, a new episode of the \u201cFuture Policy Forum\u201d, in the presence of Prof. Hisham Arafat, Vice Chairman of the Board of Trustees and Professor of Engineering at Future University in Egypt (FUE), via live broadcast through technology \u00abzoom\u00bb, sponsored by Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nRead More\nBritish Ambassador to Cairo: Education is the key to the future for Egypt\nhttps://www.almasryalyoum.com/news/details/601744\nThe British Ambassador to Cairo, John Casson, said that education is the key to Egypt's future, adding in his speech during the launch of Malvern Egypt College that Britain leads the world in this field.\r\n\r\n\u00a0The British ambassador explained: \"Today we are launching a new international school with British roots and an Egyptian future, and it is the latest in a long series of British investments in Egypt's greatest resource ever, represented in its youth.\"\r\n\r\nThe college is scheduled to open in 2016, and it is the first time that a British higher college has opened an international branch in Egypt.\r\n\r\nThe celebration was attended by Prince Michael, Prince of Kent, cousin of Queen Elizabeth II, former British Prime Minister, Tony Blair, members of the All-Party Parliamentary Group on Egypt in the British Parliament, and some of the best British talents in acting and singing, including actress Liz Hurley and singer Gabriel, to revive Entertainment in the evening.\r\n\r\nThe event was organized by Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman and CEO of Azazy International Group, which operates a number of independent schools in Egypt and the Future University in Egypt (FUE).\nRead More\nKhaled Azazy: The Council of Future University in Egypt seeks to enter the international rankings .. and the award of the late Hassan Azazy for the best scientific research\nhttps://www.alsbbora.info/69200\nDr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), confirmed that the University Council hopes that it will enter the world rankings, which is of paramount importance to them during the coming period, in addition to research, innovations, and the level of education provided to university students.\nRead More\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) celebrates the graduation of its tenth class at Al-Manara Center\nhttps://www.kashqol.com/41904\nOn Sunday, September 22, Future University in Egypt (FUE)\u00a0celebrated the graduation of the two batches of the Faculty of Pharmaceutical Sciences and Pharmaceutical Industries and the Faculty of Computers and Information Technology for the academic year 2018/2019.\nRead More\nFuture University in Egypt holds a new episode of the Policy Forum.. tomorrow\nhttps://www.awanmasr.com/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u0639\u0642\u062f-\u062d\u0644\u0642\u0629-\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629-\u0645\u0646-\u0645\u0646\u062a\u062f\nTomorrow, Tuesday, the Faculty of Economics and Political Science at Future University in Egypt (FUE)\u00a0will hold a new episode of the \u201cFuture Policy Forum\u201d at twelve o'clock in the afternoon.\r\n\r\nWhere Dr. Hisham Arafat, Vice Chairman of the Board of Trustees and Professor of Engineering at Future University in Egypt (FUE), will attend, via live broadcast through \u201czoom\u201d technology, under the auspices of Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University in Egypt (FUE).\nRead More\nKhaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt, recently signed on behalf of the university a cooperation agreement with the prestigious Rome-La Sapienza University in the Italian capital, Rome.\nhttps://archive.aawsat.com/details.asp?issueno=11700&article=588136#.YrM_y1RByM8\nChairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), recently signed on behalf of the university a cooperation agreement with the prestigious Rome-La Sapienza University in the Italian capital, Rome, and the agreement was signed on behalf of the Italian University by its president, Luigi Fratti. Under the agreement, it will conduct joint research with the Faculty of Architecture at the University of Rome in the fields of architecture, interior architecture and industrial design.\nRead More\nFuture University in Egypt opens the door for direct admission to students of equivalent degrees for the new academic year 2022-2023\nhttps://taleemalyoum.com/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u0641\u062a\u062d-\u0628\u0627\u0628-\u0627\u0644\u0642\u0628\u0648\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0628\u0627\u0634/\nDr. Ebada Sarhan, President of Future University in Egypt (FUE), announced the opening of direct registration for admission to university faculties for the academic year 2022-2023 for students of Arab and foreign equivalent certificates and their equivalent certificates at the university headquarters.\r\n\r\nHe explained that the university's board of trustees, headed by Dr. Khaled Al-Azazy, the council's president and first founder, provides all the care and support required for the university in order to provide a distinguished educational service, as the university has deep partnerships in the academic aspect and student exchange programs with major international universities.\nRead More\nThe university provides the best educational service to graduate new generations of entrepreneurs in the local and international market - Future University in Egypt is a model for global smart universities\nhttps://alwafd.news/\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631-\u0648\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0631/3938049-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0646\u0645\u0648\u0630\u062c-\u0644\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0630\u0643\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0645\u064a\u0629\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) occupies a prominent position, and an advanced rank in the world rankings of universities, as the university works to provide a strong educational system that contributes to building an enlightened and creative personality, through high-quality educational and training services, provided to its students according to the latest methods of education in the world, under the auspices of Dr. Khaled Azazy, President The Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), which is keen to develop programs for the university that depend on keeping pace with the strategic directions of the Egyptian state, especially in the education sector, and graduating effective generations capable of participating in development and competition in the local and international labor market.\nRead More\nChairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt, Khaled Azazy: The university\u2019s faculties are ready to receive new and old students in the new academic year\nhttps://alwafd.news/\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631-\u0648\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0631/3942671-\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633-\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633-\u0623\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0621-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0643\u0644\u064a\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u062c\u0627\u0647\u0632\u0629-\u0644\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0627\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0628-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u062c\u062f\u064a\u0646-\u0648\u0627\u0644\u0642\u062f\u0627\u0645\u0649-\u0641\u0649-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0645-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0649-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\nOpening the door for direct admission to receive the high school campaign last year and students of equivalent and Al-Azhar secondary certificates\r\nThe Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), headed by Dr. Khaled Al-Azazy, Chairman of the Council and its first founder, announced the readiness of the university\u2019s faculties to receive new and old students, and all faculties were equipped with all the necessary tools of the educational process to receive the new academic year. He added that based on the agreement of Dr. Khaled Abdel Ghaffar, Minister of Higher Education, it was decided to open The door for direct application to the university\u2019s admission office for students who have obtained high school and Azhar for the academic year 2019/2020 and students of Arab and foreign equivalent certificates for the academic year 2019/2020 and 2020/2021. Khaled Al-Azzazi explained that Future University in Egypt (FUE)\u00a0is working seriously and effectively to re-change the face of education in line with the requirements of sustainable development and the vision of the political leadership 2030, by relying on innovation, creativity, technology and scientific research, and providing the latest methods of smart education, and the university has achieved advanced positions in scientific research and achieved international achievements. In this regard,\r\nUntil it became a model for the modern educational institution.\nRead More\nTamer Hosny ignites the atmosphere at Future University in Egypt's celebration party (With Photos)\nhttps://www.darelhilal.com/News/1075162.aspx\nThe artist Tamer Hosni performed a concert at Future University in Egypt, and thousands of university students and fans were keen to attend the concert. Tamer achieved the largest public attendance in the history of Future University in Egypt (FUE), with the attendance of 20,000 people, at the ceremony held under the patronage of Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE). During the ceremony, Tamer Hosni presented a bouquet of his most famous songs, which witnessed a great interaction from the audience, in addition to the songs of his latest album, \"Khaleek Foulathy\", and the single, which he recently released, \"Sa3ba\".\nRead More\nFuture University in Egypt celebrates the graduation of its tenth class at Al-Manara International Conference Center\nhttps://www.youm7.com/story/2019/10/1/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u062d\u062a\u0641\u0644-\u0628\u062a\u062e\u0631\u064a\u062c-\u062f\u0641\u0639\u062a\u0647\u0627-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0634\u0631\u0629-\u0628\u0645\u0631\u0643\u0632-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0631\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u0649-\u0644\u0644\u0645\u0624\u062a\u0645\u0631\u0627\u062a/4439656\nIn a huge ceremony, Future University in Egypt (FUE) celebrated, on Sunday, September 22, the graduations of the two batches of the Faculty of Pharmaceutical Sciences and Pharmaceutical Industries and the Faculty of Computers and Technology for the academic year 2018/2019, where graduation certificates were handed over to all graduates in the presence of: Dr. Karim Badr, representative of pharmacists in Cairo, and Dr. Ebada Sarhan, President of the university, in addition to a number of leaders and deans of faculties and a number of eminent personalities, including Prof. Dr. El-Sayed Abdel Sattar, head of the Syndicate of Scientists.\nRead More\nFuture University in Egypt opens its doors to accept holders of equivalent Arab and foreign degrees\nhttps://alwafd.news/\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631-\u0648\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0631/3848623-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u0641\u062a\u062d-\u0623\u0628\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0647\u0627-\u0644\u0642\u0628\u0648\u0644-\u062d\u0645\u0644\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0634\u0647\u0627\u062f\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629-\u0648\u0627\u0644\u0623\u062c\u0646\u0628\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0627\u062f\u0644\u0629\nThe Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), headed by Dr. Khaled Al-Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees and its first founder, agreed to open the door for admission to the university\u2019s faculties for holders of Arab and foreign equivalent degrees. Applicants are nominated for admission to the university\u2019s faculties, which include Pharmacy, Oral and Dental Medicine, Engineering, Commerce, Business Administration, Computers and Information Technology.\nIn partnership with University of Cincinnati in the United States of America, University College Cork in Ireland, and University of Utara in Malaysia.\nThe university organizes university classes to teach academic programs and courses in English. It depends on distance education by organizing workshops and training courses.\nUniversity President Dr. Ebada Sarhan confirmed that the admission criteria include non-Egyptian students and Egyptian students, provided they obtain international certificates.\nRead More\nKhaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt: We seek to enter into the world rankings of universities\nhttps://www.youm7.com/story/2017/1/31/\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633-\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633-\u0623\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0621-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0646\u0623\u0645\u0644-\u062f\u062e\u0648\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0635\u0646\u064a\u0641-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0649/3080832\nDr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), confirmed that the University Council hopes it will enter the world rankings, which is of paramount importance to them during the coming period, in addition to research, innovation, and the level of education provided to university students.\nToday, Tuesday, during the activities of the International Conference on Pharmaceutical Sciences in its fourth session, which is organized by the university in a Cairo hotel and will continue until February 2, Azazy stressed that the university has held many international conferences in various fields, stressing his happiness with the participation of thirty foreign scientists from international universities. At the conference this year, the university is proud of that.\nRead More\nFuture University in Egypt applies the best smart systems in distance education\nhttps://www.vetogate.com/4255301\nDr. Hisham Arafat, Vice-Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), confirmed that the university disseminates the concept of \"interactive education\", and provides an innovative learning environment for its students within the framework of the Future University's keenness on the success of the educational process, and facing the repercussions of the spread of the Corona virus, and in its concern for the health and safety of students and members of the staff. Teaching, the university continues to complete the study of curricula and research through interactive education, through its smart platform by broadcasting lectures.\nThis comes in light of the university\u2019s commitment to the decision of the Ministry of Higher Education and Scientific Research to take exceptional measures to confront the Corona pandemic, under the guidance and patronage of Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nRead More\nAmerican Stanford chooses the Egyptian Al-Moataz Youssef among the best 2% of the world's scientists\nhttps://www.elbalad.news/4575399\nA new scientific achievement achieved by Future University in Egypt (FUE) at the international level in culmination of the efforts being made in the field of developing the educational process under the auspices and direct support of Khaled Al-Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt.\nThis new scientific achievement is represented in obtaining the classification of Dr. Al-Moataz Youssef among the top 2% of distinguished scientists in the world according to the international classification carried out by the American Stanford University.\nThe importance and scientific value of this achievement comes from the fact that Dr. Al-Moataz Youssef is the only representative of Future University in Egypt in this international classification, which is of great importance to educational institutions all over the world.\nThe Minister of Higher Education attends the graduation ceremony of Future University in Egypt students\nhttps://www.masrawy.com/news/news_egypt/details/2018/9/25/1433346/\u0628\u0627\u0644\u0635\u0648\u0631-\u0648\u0632\u064a\u0631-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0639\u0644\u064a\u0645-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0644\u064a-\u064a\u0634\u0647\u062f-\u062d\u0641\u0644-\u062a\u062e\u0631\u062c-\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0628-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644\nYesterday, Monday evening, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, Dr. Khaled Abdel Ghaffar, witnessed the ceremony held by Future University in Egypt (FUE) at the Al-Manara Center for International Conferences and Exhibitions in Cairo; On the occasion of the graduation of the class of 2018 of its students and honoring the master\u2019s and doctoral degrees, in the presence of Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the University\u2019s Board of Trustees, Dr. Ebada Sarhan, President of the University, Dr. Yasser Al-Gendi, President of the Dentists Syndicate, Dr. Hafez Al-Ghandour, President of the Syndicate of Commerce, the Vice Presidents and Deans of the University And college agents, a number of professors and public figures.\nKhaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt: We have achieved great success in \u201cinteractive education\u201d .. We are keen to keep pace with technological development .. We are ready to take the first semester exams in light of the precautionary measures\nhttps://www.youm7.com/story/2021/2/18/\u062e\u0627\u0644\u062f-\u0639\u0632\u0627\u0632\u0649-\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633-\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633-\u0623\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0621-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062d\u0642\u0642\u0646\u0627-\u0646\u062c\u0627\u062d\u0627-\u0643\u0628\u064a\u0631\u0627/5212641\nKhaled Azazy:\nStudent and faculty safety is our top priority\nWe are committed to social responsibility and the university's activities have increased in light of the Corona crisis\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) is a pioneer in launching humanitarian initiatives and organizing medical convoys\nInvesting in \"distance education\" is a win-win situation for all... and cooperation programs with international universities qualify students for the international labor market\nThe Egyptian state, under the leadership of President Abdel-Fattah El-Sisi, has placed the issue of human development as a top priority\nThe culture of \u201cArtificial Intelligence\u201d must be reinforced through the curricula and study programs offered to students.\nBreaking News: Future University in Egypt enters the QS World University Rankings for the year 2023\nhttps://www.alshouranews.com/1965414/\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u062f\u062e\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0635\u0646\u064a\u0641-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0645\u064a--QS-World-University-Rankings--\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0645-2023\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) ranked 1001-1200, in the global rankings (QS) for the year 2023, for the university to achieve a new achievement in its path full of achievements, in culmination of the continuous efforts made by the university to develop and update the diverse teaching curricula among students, within the framework of the care and support given by Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University, which is keen to promote academic excellence and continuously develop the educational process.\nFaculty of Oral and Dental Medicine at Future University in Egypt: a comprehensive academic and health institution\nhttps://www.vetogate.com/4266891\nAn unprecedented development witnessed by the Faculty of Oral and Dental Medicine at Future University in Egypt (FUE), which is one of the leading faculty in dental education, promoting scientific research, and patient care.\nThe faculty follows the highest standards of education through the implementation of a dynamic curriculum besides focusing on clinical training, and always strives to achieve excellence at the highest level and according to the most accurate standards to provide a distinguished service to its students and the community, which made it enjoy a high national and international reputation, as preparing qualified dentists comes at the forefront of its priorities. We are committed to providing quality patient care, in line with national needs and goals, with the support and care of Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nFuture University in Egypt: The beacon of education in Egypt\nhttps://alshrqalawsat.com/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0631\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0639\u0644\u064a\u0645-\u0641\u064a-\u0645\u0635\u0631/\nThe Lighthouse of Education in Egypt, it is the Future University in Egypt (FUE), which is led by an elite of the largest doctors and faculty members, headed by Dr. Khaled Al-Azzazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees.\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE), which has become the ring of hope for students in Egypt with its faculties, has been able to reach the world thanks to its high educational level in Egypt.\nFuture University in Egypt achieves an international achievement in the field of artificial intelligence in cooperation with the University of Bonn, Germany.\nhttps://warqawqalam.com/\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0639\u0644\u064a\u0645/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u062d\u0642\u0642-\u0627\u0646\u062c\u0627\u0632\u0627-\u062f\u0648\u0644\u064a\u0627-\u0641\u0649-\u0645\u062c/\nAs a culmination of the efforts made by Future University in Egypt (FUE) to keep pace with the developments of artificial intelligence technology, under the patronage and support of Dr. Khaled Azazy, a cooperation agreement between Future University in Egypt and the University of Bonn in Germany. According to the agreement, Dr. Sameh supervises students from both universities during their graduate research studies.\nKhaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt: We have achieved great success in \"interactive education\"... and we are ready to take the first semester exams in light of the precautionary measures\nhttps://www.alshoura.news/1931263/\u062e\u0627\u0644\u062f-\u0639\u0632\u0627\u0632\u0649-\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633-\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633-\u0623\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0621-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062d\u0642\u0642\u0646\u0627-\u0646\u062c\u0627\u062d\u0627-\u0643\u0628\u064a\u0631\u0627-\u0641\u0649-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0639\u0644\u064a\u0645-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0639\u0644\u0649-\u0648\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0639\u062f\u0648\u0646-\u0644\u0625\u062c\u0631\u0627\u0621-\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0641\u0635\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0631\u0627\u0633\u0649-\u0627\u0644\u0623\u0648\u0644-\u0641\u0649-\u0638\u0644-\u0627\u0644\u0625\u062c\u0631\u0627\u0621\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0627\u062d\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0632\u064a\u0629\nWe are keen to keep pace with technological development.. The safety of students and faculty is our top priority\nWe are committed to social responsibility and the university's activities have increased in light of the Corona crisis\nFuture University is a pioneer in launching humanitarian initiatives and organizing medical convoys\nInvesting in \u201cdistance education\u201d is a win-win situation.. Cooperation programs with international universities qualify students for the international labor market\nThe Egyptian state, under the leadership of President Abdel-Fattah El-Sisi, has placed the issue of human development as a top priority\nThe culture of \u201cArtificial Intelligence\u201d must be reinforced through the curricula and study programs offered to students\nFuture University in Egypt: A young scientific edifice that competes with the major prestigious universities in Egypt | Educational services at the highest level in compatibility with the requirements of the local and international labor markets | Continuous progress in the international classification of \u201cQS\u201d worldwide university rankings in the region\nhttps://www.innfrad.com/News/14/2153558/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0635\u0631\u062d-\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0649-\u0634\u0627\u0628-\u064a\u0646\u0627\u0641\u0633-\u0643\u0628\u0631\u064a\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0642\u0629\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) is one of the most important private universities in Egypt. It is a young university that stands tall among the major prestigious universities in Egypt. It has also become competitive with modern international universities in the Arab region. Future University in Egypt (FUE)\u00a0occupies a prominent position among Egyptian universities, providing educational services at a world-class level and with the latest advanced educational patterns. Technology transfer and innovation, interaction with the community in its various institutions, as well as excellence through conducting high-quality and impact research.\nPerhaps the most prominent characteristic of the Future University in Egypt (FUE)\u00a0is its good reputation and its national role, which is never separated from its academic role and its impact on global research, as this comes in accordance with elaborate plans and programs and with the sponsorship and direct support of Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), who works to promote academic excellence and develop education As an imperative to achieve sustainable development.\n\u201cYour Future\u201d at \u201cFuture University in Egypt\u201d: 10 factors that put the university in the top ranks of international universities\nhttps://www.alshouranews.net/1929317/\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644\u0643-\u0641\u0649-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-10-\u0639\u0648\u0627\u0645\u0644-\u0648\u0636\u0639\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0641\u0649-\u0645\u0635\u0627\u0641-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0627\u062a-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0645\u064a\u0629\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) is one of the leading universities, which occupies a prominent position among private universities, and occupies an advanced position in the \u201cQS\u201d world ranking of universities for the Arab region for the year 2021. Dr. Khaled Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of Future University in Egypt (FUE), which works to promote academic excellence and develop education as an imperative to achieve sustainable development and the state\u2019s vision for 2030.\nFuture University celebrates the graduation of the seventh batch of Bachelor's degrees on the music of Omar Khairat.. Photos\nhttps://www.elbalad.news/2931618\nToday, September 11, 2017, Future University celebrated the graduation of the seventh batch of students from the Faculty of Oral and Dental Medicine for the academic year 2017/2018, in the presence of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the University\u2019s Board of Trustees, Dr. Obada Sarhan, President of the University, the Syndicate of Dentists of Egypt, leaders and deans of faculties and a number of prominent figures in the academic field .\nFuture students present \u201cHamlet and the Million\u201d at Al-Gomhoria Theater today\nhttps://www.vetogate.com/1808105\nDirector Khaled Galal and Head of the Cultural Production Affairs Sector presents the latest theatrical performances \"Hamlet of the Million\" by the Future University Troupe, as part of the activities of the National Festival for Al-Masry Theater in its eighth session headed by director Nasser Abdel Moneim, and that is only today at Al-Gomhoria Theater at ten o'clock in the evening.\nThe play is produced by the Future University, a dramaturgy and poems by Dr. Mustafa Selim about Hamlet by William Shakespeare, composed by: Haitham Al-Khamisi, decor: Hazem Shebl, costumes: Marwa Odeh, reviews: Magdy Saber, executive director: Ola Fahmy, directed by: Khaled Galal, and starring elite students of the Future University Under the auspices of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the University.\nFuture University issues a statement regarding the system and dates of exams for the end of the first semester\nhttps://www.youm7.com/story/2021/1/14/\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u0635\u062f\u0631-\u0628\u064a\u0627\u0646\u0627-\u0628\u0634\u0623\u0646-\u0646\u0638\u0627\u0645-\u0648\u0645\u0648\u0627\u0639\u064a\u062f-\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0627\u062a-\u0646\u0647\u0627\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0641\u0635\u0644/5158022\nThe Future University issued a statement regarding the system and dates of the exams for the fall semester 2020, and also clarified through the statement the foundations on which the university is going in the coming weeks, under the auspices of Dr. Ministers of the Arab Republic of Egypt regarding educational policy during the academic year 2020/2021, and in light of the continuing concern over the repercussions of the second wave of the Corona virus that is affecting all parts of the globe, and in the first place for the benefit and safety of future university students and their families, faculty members and university workers, and to facilitate them, The University Council held an emergency session to lay the foundations for the university in the coming weeks, bearing in mind the proper functioning of the educational process and achieving the interest and safety of our students above all else.\nTamer Hosny shines in front of 20,000 in a concert at the Future University \"Sour\"\nhttps://www.elwatannews.com/news/details/5836153\nThe star Tamer Hosny performed a distinguished concert at the Future University, in the presence of thousands of university students and his fans, who were keen to flock to the concert venue several hours before its launch, as the audience exceeded all expectations, and Tamer achieved the largest audience attendance in the history of the Future University, with the attendance of 20 thousand people, at the ceremony. Which was held under the patronage of Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nPictures| Tamer Hosny presents a singing talent for the first time at the University of the Future concert\nhttps://www.masrawy.com/arts/music/details/2021/12/3/2134332/\u0635\u0648\u0631-\u062a\u0627\u0645\u0631-\u062d\u0633\u0646\u064a-\u064a-\u0642\u062f\u0645-\u0645\u0648\u0647\u0628\u0629-\u063a\u0646\u0627\u0626\u064a\u0629-\u0644\u0623\u0648\u0644-\u0645\u0631\u0629-\u0628\u062d\u0641\u0644-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644\nThe artist, Tamer Hosni, was keen to present a new singing talent for the first time in his concert at the Future University.\nTamer published the photos, through his account on Instagram, and commented: \"A million greetings to the youth of the Future University at today's party... Seriously, an unusual party, a great spirit, great energy, and an unnatural reception of love and welcome.\"\nHe continued: \"By God, I love you more, and I wish each one success. Thank you to the youth, management and professors of the University of the Future, thank you to the president of the university, Professor Khaled Al-Azzazi.\nTamer Hosny on the Future University party: class and honorable spirit\nhttps://www.elbalad.news/5069401\nThe artist, Tamer Hosni, shared photos from the Future University party, through his personal account on the social networking site Instagram.\nHe wrote: \u201cA million greetings to the youth of the Future University, at today\u2019s party, a party that is not an ordinary one, a great spirit, great energy, and an unnatural reception of love and welcome. Professor Khaled Al-Azzazi, I will not recommend you for the grades of the work of the year \ud83d\ude00 Your university students deserve it, I swear by God, order, class and an honorable spirit, and a very big thank you to the geniuses of Arab theater and Dania Hariri, the singing talent that he presented for the first time.\u201d\nIn pictures.. Tamer Hosny ignites the \"University of the Future\" with a distinguished concert.. And he shines in the presence of thousands\nhttps://www.alshouranews.net/1951235/\u0628\u0627\u0644\u0635\u0648\u0631-\u062a\u0627\u0645\u0631-\u062d\u0633\u0646\u0649-\u064a\u0634\u0639\u0644-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0628\u062d\u0641\u0644-\u063a\u0646\u0627\u0626\u0649-\u0645\u0645\u064a\u0632-\u0648\u064a\u062a\u0623\u0644\u0642-\u0628\u062d\u0636\u0648\u0631-\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0644\u0622\u0641\nThe star Tamer Hosny performed a distinguished concert at the Future University, in the presence of thousands of university students and his fans, who were keen to flock to the concert venue several hours before its launch. Which was held under the patronage of Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nChairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University in Egypt, contributed to the university\u2019s launch of a series of meetings and Ramadan evenings\nhttps://archive.aawsat.com/details.asp?section=68&article=583794&issueno=11593#.YrhZk1RByCh\nChairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University in Egypt, contributed to the university\u2019s launch of a series of meetings and Ramadan evenings that will continue throughout the blessed month of Ramadan under the title \u201cThe Tolerance of Islam\u201d, and it addresses the meanings of tolerance and giving in Islam, and sheds light on these meanings in front of the young generation.\nThe Minister of Higher Education attends the graduation ceremony of the students of the University of the Future\nhttp://portal.mohesr.gov.eg/ar-eg/Pages/EventsDetails.aspx?eventID=453&lst=\u0627\u0644\u0627\u062d\u062f\u0627\u062b\nDr. witnessed. Khaled Abdel Ghaffar, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, yesterday evening, Monday evening, the ceremony held by the Future University at the Al-Manara Center for International Conferences and Exhibitions in Cairo; On the occasion of the graduation of the class of 2018 of its students and honoring the holders of master\u2019s and doctoral degrees, in the presence of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the University\u2019s Board of Trustees, Dr. Obada Sarhan, President of the University, Dr. Yasser Al-Jundi, President of the Syndicate of Dentists, Dr. Hafez Al-Ghandour, President of the Syndicate of Commerce, and the Vice Presidents The university, deans and deans of faculties, a number of professors and public figures.\nIn pictures.. Omar Khairat performs the graduation ceremony of Future University students\nhttps://www.kashqol.com/16213\nYesterday, Monday, Future University celebrated the graduation of the eighth batch of students of the Faculty of Dentistry and the ninth batch of students of the Faculty of Economics and Political Science for the academic year 2018/2019, where certificates were delivered to all graduates in the presence of: Dr. Khaled Abdel Ghaffar, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, and Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University, Dr. Yasser Al-Jundi, President of the Dentists Syndicate, Dr. Hafez Al-Ghandour, President of the Commercial Syndicate, and Dr. Obada Sarhan, President of the University, in addition to a number of leaders and deans of faculties and a number of prominent personalities, including Dr. Mustafa Al-Sayed and journalist Magdi Al-Jallad. At Al-Manara International Conference Center, the great musician Omar Khairat's orchestra is playing.\nIn pictures, Marwa Nagy shines at the Future University breakfast party\nhttps://www.washwasha.org/344450\nSinger Marwa Nagy revived the Future University Iftar party inside a major hotel in New Cairo, in the presence of many art stars and celebrities.\nThe president of the university's board of directors was Dr. Khaled Azazi welcomed the audience, including businessman Ahmed Abu Hashima, singing star Hakim, and a large number of society men and celebrities.\nMarwa Nagy at the Future University Iftar | bell magazine\nhttps://aljaras.com/\u0645\u0631\u0648\u0629-\u0646\u0627\u062c\u064a-\u0641\u064a-\u0625\u0641\u0637\u0627\u0631-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644/\nEgyptian singer Marwa Nagy performed the Future University breakfast party inside a major hotel in New Cairo, in the presence of many art stars and celebrities.\nThe Chairman of the University's Board of Directors, Dr. Khaled Azazi, welcomed the audience, including businessman Ahmed Abu Hashima, singing star Hakim, and a large number of society men and celebrities.\nThrough \u201czoom\u201d technology, the University of the Future holds a \u201cFuture Policy Forum\u201d\nhttps://elbashayer.com/2699441/\u0639\u0628\u0631-\u062a\u0642\u0646\u064a\u0629-zoom-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u062a\u0639\u0642\u062f-\u0645\u0646\u062a\u062f/\nThe Faculty of Economics and Political Science at the Future University will hold, the day after tomorrow, Tuesday, at noon, a new episode of the \u201cFuture Policy Forum\u201d, in the presence of Prof. Dr. Hisham Arafat, Vice Chairman of the Board of Trustees and Professor of Engineering at Future University, via live broadcast through technology \u00abzoom\u00bb, sponsored by Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nThe annual Future University Cultural Festival kicks off at the Opera House\nhttps://www.shorouknews.com/news/view.aspx?cdate=11052017&id=8590a3ca-77a9-46b7-ab57-644278ece085\nThe annual cultural festival at the Future University was launched under the auspices of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees, and in the presence of the university president, Dr. Obada Sarhan, the university\u2019s vice presidents, deans, agents, university professors, and a group of plastic art experts, at the Egyptian Opera House.\nIn pictures.. Future University celebrates the graduation of the seventh batch of \"Dentistry\"\nhttps://www.albawabhnews.com/2706563\nThe Future University celebrated yesterday, Monday, the graduation of the seventh batch of students of the Faculty of Oral and Dental Medicine for the academic year 2017/2018, in the presence of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the University\u2019s Board of Trustees, Dr. Obada Sarhan, President of the University, the Syndicate of Dentists of Egypt, leaders and deans of faculties, and a number of prominent figures in the academic field.\nThe University of the Future organizes graduation ceremonies for all faculties over a period of 4 days, where each batch will graduate each day separately, to the tunes of the great musician Omar Khairat, whose students will celebrate their graduation to the tunes of his music. September 2017, and the celebration activities will be held in the Grand Theater of the Egyptian Opera House, where the first ceremony witnessed honoring the first batch and handing out certificates to all graduates.\nFuture University is preparing for the first semester exams amid strict precautionary measures\nhttps://www.kashqol.com/73413\nThe University of the Future is working on completing all preparations for the first semester exams scheduled for next January, which include many precautionary and preventive measures for the safety of students and workers, under the auspices of Dr. Masks and disinfection tools for distribution to students.\nA new episode of the Policy Forum at the University of the Future.. today\nhttps://www.awanmasr.com/\u062d\u0644\u0642\u0629-\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629-\u0645\u0646-\u0645\u0646\u062a\u062f\u0649-\u0627\u0644\u0633\u064a\u0627\u0633\u0627\u062a-\u0628\u0640-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627/\nToday, at 12 noon, the Faculty of Economics and Political Science at Future University will hold a new episode of the \u201cFuture Policies Forum\u201d in the .\nDr. Hisham Arafat, Vice Chairman of the Board of Trustees and Professor of Engineering at the Future University, will attend, via live broadcast through \u201czoom\u201d technology, under the auspices of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University.\nThe University of the Future is making great progress in the international rankings of universities in the Arab region\nhttps://www.vetogate.com/4442993\nAs a result of the continuous efforts made by the Future University to develop and update the diverse curricula and teaching methods among students in various faculties, it has been able to achieve great strides in the international rankings (QS) ranking, as it was crowned for the year 2022 by the (World Universities Ranking) for the Arab region in the 51st place. 60 among Arab universities, ranked No. 7 among public universities, and ranked first among private universities in Egypt.\nThis achievement comes in the international classification of the University of the Future in appreciation of the university\u2019s research and educational services on a global level in line with the latest advanced educational patterns and according to elaborate plans and programs, under the auspices of Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University, who is constantly keen to enhance academic excellence and develop Education as an imperative to achieve sustainable development and Egypt's 2030 development vision.\nThe National Authority grants educational quality to the Faculty of Economics and Political Science at Future University\nhttps://www.cairo24.com/1362672\nThe Faculty of Economics and Political Science at the Future University in Egypt obtained accreditation from the Board of Directors of the National Authority for Quality Assurance of Education and Academic and Educational Accreditation at its last meeting, to add the university to its previous achievements under the auspices of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University in Egypt.\nThe French ambassador honors the University of the Future and the heroes of my beloved, my homeland\nhttps://www.hiamag.com/\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0641\u064a\u0631-\u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0646\u0633\u064a-\u064a\u0643\u0631\u0645-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644-\u0648\u0623\nNicolas Gallet, the French ambassador in Cairo, praised the makers of the operetta \"Habibi Ya Watan\", which was presented by the Future University at the end of the sixth festival for university students, which was held at the Egyptian Opera House. This came during the honoring ceremony that was held by his community inside his home in Giza to honor Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the university and the heroes of the national opera, in the presence of the stars of \"Habibi Ya Watan\" Hani Shaker, Medhat Saleh, Latifa, director Khaled Galal, poet Nader Abdullah, composer Walid Saad and narrator of the opera. Artist Ahmed Badir. The artist Tamer Abdel Moneim, the journalist Mohamed Fouda, the businessman Hani Al-Shamy, the tourist expert Amr Badr, and a group of members of the diplomatic corps also attended. During his speech, the French ambassador thanked Al-Azzazi and his educational institution for supporting and sponsoring a distinguished national artistic work that contributes to the stability of the Egyptian situation and urges solidarity for the advancement of the country. Gallet announced his full support for such actions as a contribution to strengthening relations between Cairo and Paris. For his part, Khaled Azazi thanked the French ambassador and his country, a friend of Egypt and the Egyptian people. He affirmed his pride in this honoring of the university and of the \"Habibi Ya Watan\" team, noting that he, as an Egyptian, is proud of this work. He expressed his happiness with everyone who participated in or supported this success because Egypt has always been the country of struggle and success and will always be so.\nMinister of Higher Education attends the graduation ceremony of the students of the University of the Future\nhttps://elahrarpress.com/2018/09/25/\u0648\u0632\u064a\u0631-\u0627\u0644\u062a\u0639\u0644\u064a\u0645-\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0644\u064a-\u064a\u0634\u0647\u062f-\u062d\u0641\u0644-\u062a\u062e\u0631\u062c-\u0637\u0644\u0627/\nDr. witnessed. Khaled Abdel Ghaffar, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, yesterday evening, Monday evening, the ceremony held by the Future University at the Al-Manara Center for International Conferences and Exhibitions in Cairo; On the occasion of the graduation of the class of 2018 of its students and honoring the holders of master\u2019s and doctoral degrees, in the presence of Dr. Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the University\u2019s Board of Trustees, Dr. Obada Sarhan, President of the University, Dr. Yasser Al-Jundi, President of the Syndicate of Dentists, Dr. Hafez Al-Ghandour, President of the Syndicate of Commerce, and the Vice Presidents The university, deans and deans of faculties, a number of professors and public figures.\nIn pictures: Omar Khairat is the star of the \"Future University\" alumni party\nhttps://www.sayidaty.net/node/222411/\u0641\u0646-\u0648\u0645\u0634\u0627\u0647\u064a\u0631/\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u0627\u0647\u064a\u0631/\u0628\u0627\u0644\u0635\u0648\u0631-\u0639\u0645\u0631-\u062e\u064a\u0631\u062a-\u0646\u062c\u0645-\u062d\u0641\u0644-\u062e\u0631\u0651\u064a\u062c\u064a-\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644\nThe musician Omar Khairat performed the graduation ceremony of the \u201c2014\u201d batch of the Faculty of Oral and Dental Medicine \u201cFuture University\u201d, in the presence of Dr. Ahmed Abdel Khaleq, Minister of Higher Education, Khaled Azazi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University, Dr. Obada Sarhan, President of the University, and Dr. Reda Abdel Rahman The Dean of the College of Oral and Dental Medicine, Dr. Yasser Al-Jundi, the Vice-Dean of the Dental Syndicate, and the Acting Captain... in addition to the deans of the faculties at the university, who participated in honoring outstanding students and handing over certificates to graduates, holders of master's and doctoral degrees, from various faculties of the university.\nGlobal outlooks bring reform to education\nhttp://www.theworldfolio.com/news/global-outlooks-bring-reform-to-education/4047/\nBased on research, innovation and internationally accredited programmes, Azazy Group\u2019s Future University Egypt is rapidly becoming a reference point in the country\u2019s education sector. Furthermore, the group\u2019s planned Knowledge City will add further innovation to a sector under change\nOne institution in particular has seen standout success in bringing international standards into the Egyptian education system. Future University Egypt (FUE), a member of the Azazy Group, has gained attention not only on a national level, but has also attracted students from around the world. \u201cThe Azazy Group has over 20,000 students, and almost 20 per cent of our students are foreign or international students from countries like the U.S., Canada, Nigeria and other Arab states,\u201d explains Chairman and CEO Khaled Azazy.\n\u2022\tHigher education reform in post-revolution Egypt\nhttps://egyptindependent.com/higher-education-reform-post-revolution-egypt/\nHigher Education Reform in Post-Revolution Egypt by Anthony J. Perzigian, PhD, Board of Trustees Chair Adviser, Future University in Egypt, and Provost and Professor Emeritus, University of Cincinnati (USA)\nSince the first of January 2011, I have had the great honor and privilege of serving as Board of Trustees Chair Adviser for Quality Assurance & Academic Affairs at the Future University in Egypt (FUE).\u00a0\u00a0 Chairman Khaled Azazy recruited me from the University of Cincinnati (USA) where I had served as professor of anthropology from 1970 to 2010 and also served as Senior Vice President for Academic Affairs and Provost for 14 years.\nEducation to promote technology and innovation towards a knowledge-based economy\nhttps://meobserver.org/education-to-promote-technology-and-innovation-towards-a-knowledge-based-economy/\n\u201cThe university was founded in 2006 and has experienced unprecedented growth, even through the revolution,\u201d says Khaled Azazy, Chairman of Azazy Group.\nIn order for Egypt to reach its goals to become a digital and knowledge-based economy, the educational sector will be crucial, and as such forms an important pillar of the nation\u2019s Vision 2030 strategy.\nIt is a sector which historically has been neglected and under-funded, leading to overcrowded classrooms and poor infrastructure. But a new drive to overhaul and modernize the system \u2013 led by Dr. Tarek Shawki, Egypt\u2019s Minister of Education and Technical Education \u2013 is already underway, and over the last four years, private and public investment in education has increased significantly.\nThe 4th International Conference for Computing and Informatics - Cairo, FUE, December 2019\nhttps://www.academia.edu/41266527/The_4th_International_Conference_for_Computing_and_Informatics_Cairo_FUE_December_2019\nUCC and Future University in Egypt (FUE) renew the Co-operation Agreement on the delivery of an enhanced BSc. Pharmacy degree in Egypt\nhttps://www.ucc.ie/en/pharmacy/events/news/ucc-and-future-university-in-egypt-fue-renew-the-co-operation-agreement-on-the-delivery-of-an-enhanced-bsc-pharmacy-degree-in-egypt.html\nPictured: Back row (Left to right) Dean Seham A. Elkheshen, Dean of Faculty of Pharmaceutical Sciences, FUE; Khaled Azazy \u2013 MBA, Chairman of FUE Board of Trustees , Ambassador Se\u00e1n O Regan, Ambassador of Ireland to Egypt, Prof Stephen Byrne, Head of School of Pharmacy, Dean of Undergraduate Studies, UCC; Front row (left to right) Prof. Patrick O\u2019Shea, President of UCC; Dr. Ebada Sarhan, President of Futures University in Egypt, Cairo.\nThe official ceremony for the renewal of the Cooperation Agreement between University College Cork and Future University in Egypt (FUE) was held at FUE on 28th January 2019.\nProfessor Ebada Sarhan, President of FUE and Professor Patrick O\u2019Shea, UCC, signed an extension agreement whereby the School of Pharmacy, UCC will continue to support the Faculty of Pharmaceutical Sciences and Pharmaceutical Industries, FUE in the delivery of an enhanced Pharmacy degree programme by FUE in Egypt.\nFuture University on QS World University Rankings 2023\nhttps://egyptian-gazette.com/entertainment/future-university-on-qs-world-university-rankings-2023/\nEgypt\u2019s Future University has ranked in the 1001-1200 band of the QS World University Rankings 2023.\nThe achievement adds to the university\u2019s copious record, and crowns ongoing tireless efforts to modernise curricula. It has been the outcome of support by Chairman of the Board of Trustees, Prof. Khaled Azazi, who is keen on further bolstering academic excellence and continuously promote the educational process.\nA premier university for the nation\u2019s future\nhttp://www.theworldfolio.com/news/a-premier-university-for-the-nations-future/3719/\n\u201cAzazy Group has been a leader in education since 1958 when my father \r\nstarted a private school,\u201d explains current Future University Chairman \r\n& CEO Khaled Azazy. \u201cSince then, 14 primary and secondary schools \r\nhave been built with the Azazy name. The university was founded in 2006 \r\nand experienced unprecedented growth, even through the revolution. FUE \r\ntargets partnerships with international universities, especially in the \r\nUSA. We are approved as an institution with a quality of education \r\nsimilar to the United States and United Kingdom. If a local or an \r\ninternational student here in Egypt is looking for education with these \r\nstandards, it is available through Azazy Group\u2019s various institutions.\u201d \r\nUnder the umbrella of the Azazy Group, Future University, Egypt is \r\nclearly on the path to creating the highest international standards for \r\nits students.\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) is a private university founded in 2006\nhttps://www.amcham.org.eg/membership/members-database/5589/future-university-in-egypt\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) is a private university founded in 2006. It comprises six faculties, a dental hospital and pharmaceutical factory. FUE aims at advancing the frontiers of knowledge and serving the society through education and research.\nKHALID AZAZY, CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES OF THE FUTURE UNIVERSITY IN EGYPT: WE'VE ACHIEVED GREAT SUCCESS IN INTERACTIVE EDUCATION, AND WE'RE KEEN TO KEEP UP WITH TECHNOLOGICAL DEVELOPMENT.\nhttps://www.fue.edu.eg/news/khalid_azazy_chairman_board_trustees_future_university_egypt\nKhalid Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University in Egypt: We've achieved great success in interactive education, and we're keen to keep up with technological development.\nKhalid Azazy, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Future University in Egypt: We've achieved great success in interactive education, and we're keen to keep up with technological development.\nWe\u2019re ready for the first semester tests under precautionary procedures and the safety of students and faculty is our top priority\nWe are committed to society responsibility and university activities increased in the Corona crisis\nFuture University in Egypt (FUE) is proactive in launching humanitarian initiatives and organizing medical convoys.\nInvesting in distance learning is a win - win. Cooperation programs with world universities qualify students for the international labor market\nThe Egyptian state, led by President Abdel Fattah Al-Sisi, has placed the issue of human development on its top priority.\nThe culture of \"artificial intelligence\" must be promoted through the curricula and programs offered to students.\nTalk about private universities and the private higher education system must include Khaled Azazy at the forefront of the scene, not as Chairman of the Board of Trustees of FUE, which is one of the most important and prominent private universities in Egypt, but as an educator who enjoys out-of-the-box visions and insights in this vital field, which is closely linked to science and technology and has become a common feature in all aspects of life."
"Future University in Egypt - FUE\nThis institution has verified its data\nScimago Institutions Rankings\nInternational Ranking\nFuture University in Egypt is present for the first time in the global ranking Scimago Institutions Rankings, where the university ranked No. 19 on Egypt, No. 93 on the Middle East and No. 739 on the world, surpassing many private and public universities. It is worth noting that Scimago Institutions Rankings is a science evaluation resource to assess worldwide universities and research focused institutions. Academic and research related institutions are ranked by a composite indicator that combines three different sets of indicators based on research performance, innovation outputs and social impact.\nQuacquarelli Symonds (QS)\nInternational Ranking 2022\nQS Arab Ranking: 51-60\nRanking Evolution:\n2020 #111-120\n2021 #71-80\n2022 #51-60\nQS Star Ranking\nQS Stars is a rating system that helps you select the right university based on your interests. It provides a detailed look at an institution, identifying which universities rate highest in the specific topics that matter to you, like facilities, graduate employability, social responsibility, inclusiveness, and more.\n4 Stars:\u00a0Overall Inclusiveness Specialist Criteria: Dentistry\n5 Stars:\u00a0Teaching Employability Facilities Social Responsibility\n3 Stars:\u00a0Internationalization Academic Development\nQS Official Listing for FUE\nTimes Higher Education - THE\nInternational Ranking 2022\nArab University Rankings 81-90\nThe Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2022 include more than 1,600 universities across 99 countries and territories, making them the largest and most diverse university rankings to date.\nThe table is based on 13 carefully calibrated performance indicators that measure an institution\u2019s performance across four areas: teaching, research, knowledge transfer and international outlook.\nThis year\u2019s ranking analyzed more than 108 million citations across over 14.4 million research publications and included survey responses from almost 22,000 scholars globally. Overall, we collected over 430,000 data points from more than 2,100 institutions that submitted data.\nQuacquarelli Symonds (QS)\nInternational Ranking 2023\nAs one of the most prestigious higher education institutions, Future University celebrates its prominent rankings which reflects FUE\u2019s dedication to promote the educational process in Egypt, the Arab region as well as Africa. According to QS World University Ranking, FUE has been ranked 1001-1200 globally (2023), THE TOP of Private Universities in Egypt, and the fourth among Egyptian universities. On the level of our continent, Future University has been ranked 10th in Africa, and the 2nd among African rated universities."
