ng and Information Technology\nFees:\n9,160 $\nThe College of Computing and Information Technology (CCIT) was established in 2003, and has earned a strong reputation for excellence in research and teaching. With close industry links, the college offers a range of innovative and flexible taught programs aimed at producing graduates with the personal and professional skills most valued by employers in Egypt and abroad.\u00a0\nThe College of Computing and Information Technology at the Arab Academy for Science, Technology, and Maritime Transport seeks to be a leading and distinguished college in teaching and learning various fields of computing and information technology, scientific research, environmental service.\nThe College graduates specialists in the fields of computing and information technology with the knowledge, technical, and professional skills. Such skills enable them to innovate, compete, and contribute to scientific research on the national and international levels, as well as to provide community-based services. This is achieved through continuous development and improvement of educational programs and scientific research utilizing an overall quality framework to contribute in the advancement of I.T. specialists while committing to human and ethical values.\nCollege of International Transport and Logistics\nFees:\n8860 $\nThe College of International Transport andLogistics was established in 1995 in order to cope with the trends in the global business market. AASTMT has established the College of International Transport and Logistics (CITL) which is the only college in the Middle East and North African regions to offer Bachelor degree in the management of trade logistics and international transport in both the Arabic and English languages.\nColleges of Language and Communication\nFees:\n9060 $\nThe Colleges of Language and Communicationstrives to become the standard of excellence for colleges in the fields of language and communication. It aspires to be 