ultural Heritage was inaugurated in September 2018. This college focuses on creating a new caliber of archaeologists and cultural heritage professionals who are capable of facing the challenges of the 21st century of the Cultural Heritage in the Middle East and Africa. The college prepares the students to work on international archaeological missions and museums. It also provides students with ample training in critical heritage studies parallel to their archaeological training, thus creating a new caliber of students that the job market needs.\nTechnical & Vocational Institute\nFees:\nTechnical & Vocational Institute seeks to become the first vocational institute in the Arab countries within 8 years towards the International level. and its mission is to efficiently integrate out technical, managerial, training, consultation and laboratory facilities to proactively create market-driven resources in order to provide high quality educational environment, help solving business problems and fulfil industrial needs."
