,\u201d IASTED 16th Int'l Conference on Applied Informatics, Germany, February 1998.\nEl-Sharkawi, M. \"Object Migration in Semantic Databases,\" IASTED 13th Int'l Conference on Applied Informatics, Austria, February 1995.\nEl-Sharkawi, M. and Kambayashi, Y. \"Generating Nested SQL Queries for Documentation,\" Transactions of Information Processing Society of Japan, Vol. 35, No. 2, Feb. 1994, pp. 253 - 266.\nEl-Sharkawi, M. \"Efficient Processing of Set SQL Queries,\" Future Databases 92, Kyoto, Japan, Edited by: Q. Chen, Y. Kambayashi, R. Sacks-Davis, World Scientific, 1992.\nEl-Sharkawi, M. and Kambayashi, Y. \"Object Migration Mechanisms to Support Updates in Object-Oriented Databases,\" in Databases: Theory, Design, and Applications, pp. 73-92, Edited by: N. Rishe, S. Navathe, D. Tal, IEEE Computer Society Press, 1991.\nEl-Sharkawi, M. and Kambayashi, Y. \"Efficient Processing of Distributed Set Queries,\" in Databases: Theory, Design, and Applications, pp. 93-109, Edited by: N. Rishe, S. Navathe, D. Tal, IEEE Computer Society Press, 1991.\nEl-Sharkawi, M., \"Answering Queries in Temporal Object-Oriented Databases,\" Database Systems for Advanced Applications'91 (DASFAA 91), Tokyo, Japan, Edited by : A. Makinouchi, World Scientific, 1991.\nEl-Sharkawi, M., Kambayashi, Y. \"Architecture and Implementation of ENLI: Example-Based Natural Language Assisted Interface,\" Proc. of PARBASE-90, Int'l. Conference on Databases, Parallel Architectures, and Their Applications, March 6-9, 1990, Florida, U. S.A.\nElgammal A., El-Sharkawi M., \"Using Process Algebra for the Automatic Verification of Composite Web Service Modeled in UML\", Al-Azhar Engineering Ninth International Conference (AEIC'07), pp. 347-366, Egypt, 2007.\nProf. Hoda Mokhtar\nTitle:\nDean Computing and Information Sciences\nProf. Hoda M. O. Mokhtar received the B.Sc. degree (Distinction with Honors) in 1997 and the M.Sc. degree in 2000 from the Department of Computer Engineering, Faculty of Engineering, Cairo University, and the Ph.D. degree in Computer Science from the University of California, Santa Barbara (UCSB), in 2005.\nDr. Hoda Mokhtar is a Professor of Data Engineering in the Information Systems Dept. at the Faculty of Computers and Artificial Intelligence. She had been the Chair of the Information Systems Department at the Faculty of Computers and Artificial Intelligence since 2019.\nShe contributed to teaching multiple courses for the undergraduate and graduate levels and supervised a number of MSc and Ph.D. theses. Her research interests include big data analytics, data warehousing, data mining, database systems, social network analysis, bioinformatics, and location-based systems. She also received multiple awards and certificates for her academic achievements.\nEducation\nPh.D. degree in Computer Science from the University of California, Santa Barbara (UCSB), in 2005.\nMasters of Science in Computer Science from the Computer Science Dept. at University of California Santa Barbara, USA.\nM.Sc. degree in 2000 from the Department of Computer Engineering, Faculty of Engineering, Cairo.\nBachelor at Cairo University, (Distinction with Honors) in 1997\nCourses Taught\nUndergraduate Level:\nIntroduction to Programming\nLogic Design\nArtificial Intelligence\nData Warehousing\nIntroduction to Data Science\nAdvanced Topics in Database Systems.\nGraduate Level:\nBioinformatics\nAdvanced Databases Systems\nAdvanced Topics in Data Engineering.\nPublications\nM. Ramadan, A. El-Kilany, H. M. O. Mokhtar and I. Sobh, \"RL_QOptimizer: A Reinforcement Learning Based Query Optimizer,\" in IEEE Access, vol. 10, pp. 70502-70515, 2022, doi: 10.1109/ACCESS.2022.3187102. (Impact factor: 3.476)\nHabib, W.M.A., Mokhtar, H.M.O. & El-Sharkawi, M.E. Discovering top-weighted k-truss communities in large graphs. Journal of Big Data 9, 36 (2022). https://doi.org/10.1186/s40537-022-00588-1(10.835 - 2 Year Impact Factor (2021))\nMariam M. Hassan and Hoda M.O. Mokhtar, \u201cAutismOnt: An 