maa Attia has added a new academic dimension by working as an academic, trainer, and consultant at many companies, which she has helped to successfully outperform their competitors. As she is a freelance marketing consultant and certified as an International Professional trainer from Missouri University, USA.\nProfessor Attia has also held senior roles in many universities public and private universities, inside Egypt and internationally; previously, Prof. Samaa Attia was the Head of Business Administration Department and the Vice \u2013 Dean of Post Graduate Studies and Research at the Faculty of Commerce, Suez University. Prior to her appointment at Suez University, she used to work at the British University in Egypt for eight years. During which, she held different posts such as E-Learning Coordinator for the Faculty of Business Administration, Economics and Political Science, Staff Development Coordinator, Teaching and Learning officer, and Library officer. Finally, before leaving, she was the director of the \u201cCenter of Innovation, Governance and Green Economy\u201d.\nShe has published many articles in International Journals discussing many topics. and she is a reviewer for many international marketing journals and conferences. Dr. Samaa acts as an external examiner and supervisor to Masters and Ph.D. theses nationally and internationally. She also teaches several Marketing courses all aimed at promoting marketing among students and preparing them to be distinguished marketers themselves.\nEducation\nPh.D. from Aston University, UK, and MBA from the Netherlands.\nResearch Interests: Branding, Religiosity, Social Media Marketing, and Green Marketing\nCourses Taught\nSales Management\nServices Marketing\nBrand Management\nMarketing Strategy and Planning\nStrategic Marketing\nMarketing Research\nPrinciples of Marketing\nInternational Marketing,\nPublic Relations and Introduction to Business.\nPublications\nProf. Samaa Taher Attia is a freelance marketing consu