"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\nThis institution has not verified its data\nDo you own \"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\" ?\nVerify it now!\nQs Ranking:\nFounded:\n2002\nResearch Centers Availability:\nNo\nNumber of Students:\nNumber of Staff:\nGender:\nMixed\nWebsite:\nhttp://www.ufe.edu.eg/\nApply for Admissions\nFounded in 2002, the Universit\u00e9 Fran\u00e7aise d\u2019\u00c9gypte (UFE) (French University in Egypt) is a higher education institution under the dual supervision of Egyptian and French ministries of higher education. The UFE offers a promise to the new generation of pathfinders. A promise to receive unparalleled high-quality educational programs, a solid integration into the job market and a dedication to securing your professional future. The hub of French higher education in Egypt, the UFE delivers a multi-cultural experience as it offers a number of degrees from acclaimed French universities, accredited by France\u2019s Ministry of Higher Education, Research and Innovation. A multidisciplinary establishment, the university\u2019s disciplines include engineering sciences, computer science and artificial intelligence, management, social sciences, architecture and applied languages. Courses are taught in French and English in an Arabic-speaking environment.\nOur academic goals are supported by a wide spectrum of strategic partnerships with France\u2019s finest educational organizations. Their expertise is passed on to our students through a diversity of courses and programs. These partners include Universit\u00e9 Paris I Panth\u00e9on-Sorbonne, Universit\u00e9 Sorbonne Nouvelle, Universit\u00e9 de Nantes, Universit\u00e9 de Haute Alsace and the INSA of Strasbourg, all of them listed in the international rankings.\n(5.00)\n1 visitors have rated this institution\nStudied or Worked here? Share Your Review\nStar Rating\nOne Star\nTwo Star\nThree Star\nFour Star\nFive Star"
"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\nThis institution has not verified its data\nDo you own \"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\" ?\nVerify it now!\nDennis Darby\nTitle:\nPresident of French University in Egypt\n2003 - Agr\u00e9gation in Management Sciences - External competition - Rank: 8th.\n1999 - Doctorate in Management Sciences (Marketing) - Paris-Dauphine University. : \"Consumer procrastination: a contribution to the explanation of postponement of purchase\" - Very Honorable Mention with Congratulations from the Jury and Grant for publication.\n1997 - Participant in the CEFAG program of the FNEGE\n1995 - DEA Marketing and Strategy - Paris-Dauphine University.\n1984 - Master of Applied Economics - Paris-Dauphine University.\n1982 - First Prize of the General Open University Competition in Economics\nMounir Fakhry Abdel Nour\nTitle:\nChairman of the Board of Trustees of French University in Egypt\nFormer Minister of Tourism\nParliamentarian expert and general secretary of the New Wafd Party\nMember of the Board of Directors of the Stock Exchange\nMember of the National Council for Human Rights\nMember of the Board of Directors of the Center for Research and Studies of Developing Countries\nDeputy in the People's Assembly in the Parliament of 2000\nDima Elhusseini\nTitle:\nVice President of French University in Egypt\nDima El Husseini\u00a0 is Vice-President of Universit\u00e9 Fran\u00e7aise d\u2019Egypte (UFE) since October 2020. She is a Professor of Applied Languages. She previously was Dean of the faculty of Applied Languages at UFE from 2018 till 2020 and previously vice-dean. She is also Vice-President of l\u2019Association internationale des Langues \u00c9trang\u00e8res Appliqu\u00e9es.\nShe defended her Ph.D. Thesis at Sorbonne Universit\u00e9 (Paris IV) in French and comparing literature. She has published in 2005 the translation from Arabic to French of the theatre play of Pr Ahmed Etman \u00ab The blind host recovers vision \u00bb. She also published the translation into French of the novel \u00ab Ahlam et Les \u00e9boueurs du Caire \u00bb from Fawziya Assaad. Her last research articles are focusing on translation and localization issues for the web."
"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\nThis institution has not verified its data\nDo you own \"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\" ?\nVerify it now!\nFaculty of Applied Languages\nFees:\n55000 EGP\nThe bachelor of Applied languages prepares to trilingual careers (French, English and Arabic) in complex economic, cultural and social environments. The program is designed with partner companies and organizations. Students will attend languages courses, civilization and cultural courses as well as management (finance and accounting). International organizations and political life is also in the scope of the program while civil and international law is proposed to the students.\nFaculty of Architecture\nFees:\nThe Bachelor of Architecture prepares to the architect career. Our future architects are able to meet the needs of the international market in general and the Egyptian one in particular, especially in the field of sustainable development. The program provides employment for students through internships taken during the years of study. The majority of them are hired by the companies where they did their internships or in other French companies or agencies established in Egypt, such as Total, Lafarge and Vinci.\nFaculty of Mechanical Engineering\nFees:\n80000 EGP\nThe program is to provide a quality education covering a broad spectrum of Mechanical Engineering specialty areas that prepares students to effectively apply engineering knowledge to the evaluation, design, operation, and maintenance of integrated governmental, industrial, and service systems.\nMaster of International Relations\nFees:\nThe master\u2019s program in International Relations was established in partnership with the Grenoble Institute of Political Studies (Sciences Po Grenoble). Taught online, it leads to a joint diploma which delivers, on the one hand, a master\u2019s degree recognized by the French Ministry of Higher Education and Research; on the other hand, an Egyptian master\u2019s degree, accredited by the Egyptian Ministry of Higher Education and Research.\nFaculty of Economics and Management\nFees:\nThe Bachelor in Economics and Management is the program of choice to get essential knowledge in management and economics and to develop abilities in quantitative techniques in a miniul of 3 years of study.\u00a0 Mastering quantitative methods is required to move to new positions such as business data analyst.\nFaculty of Computer Engineering\nFees:\nThe Computer Engineering program aims to train specialists and professionals, mastering both fundamental computer skills and modern techniques of today and able to assimilate those of tomorrow."
"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\nThis institution has not verified its data\nDo you own \"Universite Francaise d'Egypte\" ?\nVerify it now!\nUniversit\u00e9 de Haute-Alsace\nhttps://www.uha.fr/fr/index.html\nWith a 40-year history, approximately 11000 students and more than 13 laboratories / research centres, these are the key facts and figures concerning the UHA. The Universit\u00e9 de Haute Alsace as a tertiary level education, training and research establishment operates on 5 campuses spread over two towns : Mulhouse and Colmar.\nThe UHA was officially founded on the 8th October 1975 and now incorporates 4 faculties, 2 engineering schools and 2 Institutes of Technology (IUTs) some of which pre-date the university itself. In fact, this is exactly the case with the two engineering schools (established in the 19th century) which were created in response to the needs of local industrialists for skilled manual workers. Ever since, the university has continued to expand and improve its education and training course portfolio and also to focus upon its research to feed into its learning and teaching programmes and enhance their professionalism and innovative nature.\nSorbonne Nouvelle Universit\u00e9 Des Culture\nhttp://www.univ-paris3.fr/\nThe Sorbonne Nouvelle offers high-level training in the field of Human and Social Sciences: Languages, Letters, Arts and Contemporary Societies. In undergraduate studies, each course offers a major-minor combination which allows the student to discover two disciplines from the first year. From the second year, the student is offered a choice: to continue the major-minor combination followed in the first year, or to opt for a \"reinforced major\" which will allow him to specialize in the discipline of his choice or even opt for a double diploma, by reinforcing the teachings of the minor.\nScience Po Grenoble\nhttp://www.sciencespo-grenoble.fr/\nFounded in 1948, Sciences Po Grenoble is one of the nine Institutes of Political Studies in 