ronics, civil engineering, surveying engineering, HVAC and energy engineering, electrical engineering) and architecture.\nAll INSA programs have the European EUR-ACE\u00ae quality label for graduate engineering degree programs, accredited in accordance with the EUR-ACE\u00ae Framework Standards and Guidelines.\nL'Universit\u00e9 Paris 1 Panth\u00e9on-Sorbonne\nhttps://www.pantheonsorbonne.fr/\nAt the heart of the Latin Quarter, Paris 1 Panth\u00e9on-Sorbonne University combines the glorious past of the college founded by Robert de Sorbon in the 13th century with an innovative multidisciplinary project. Since 1970, it has established its training and research mission around three major scientific poles: human sciences and the arts, law and political science as well as economics and management.\nEstablished on 25 sites in Paris and Ile-de-France, it supports more than 43,000 students per year in a civic and humanist approach. At the heart of a network of international relations spanning five continents, the university plays a major role in the training of researchers, professors, magistrates, lawyers, executives for companies and the administration. Its motto is: Omnibus sapientia, unicuique excellentia - Knowledge for all, excellence for everyone.\nWith 800 years of history and 50 years of excellence, the University of Paris 1 Panth\u00e9on-Sorbonne is today the largest university of human and social sciences in France."
